Results.ReviewText: I recently came across this coffee and am so glad I did. As a child, I used to spend 2p of my 7p weekly pocket money on a sachet of Nescafe original. My parents were tea drinkers but I was born a coffee lover. Nescafe Gold barista style is a truly authentic barista tasting coffee, a party on the taste buds! It has all the taste of fresh ground but none of the mess or hassle of cleaning out cafetieres or machines. The advantage too is stays hotter as no machine involved. Truly lovely, smooth, full-flavoured robust coffee, with the exceptional quality one has come to expect from Nescafe! Excellent.
Results.Title: Barista style taste without the fuss in an instant

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend Barista Style Coffee is perfect for Coffee lovers that love the deep rich flavour of the roast , while it may appear to be more expensive than other coffees the Flavour more than makes up for the price , after all if you walked into a Coffee shop you'd be paying more for 2 cups than for an entire Carton . I have 2 ways of drinking this , either black and very strong or it makes a fantastic Latte just heat some milk in the microwave with a sprinkling of cinnamon then add 2 heaped teaspoons of coffee and top up with Hot water , it creates a delicious milky foam and keeps you coming back for more !
Results.Title: Barista style Coffee at Home

Results.ReviewText: From the moment I poured in the water on top of my heaped tea spoon of Nescafe Gold Barista style coffee it was pure bliss from the smell of the coffee invoking memoires of me in London a student ordering my first expresso from a very large Italian gentleman who told me “maybe you try a latte” but I thought been a woman of the world I’d be well able for it.  He was right I couldn’t even try a second sip.  Been the nice Italian man that he was he fired up his machine and produced a froughty milky mug and popped my expresso into it.  It was lovely I enjoyed it so much.  That was nearly 30 years ago but the smell and taste of the barista style coffee is timeless.
Results.Title: Hidden Memeries

Results.ReviewText: I bought this after my usual instant was sold out and I now have a new favourite! It's gorgeous flavour & smell brings the coffee shop to your kitchen. For me, anytime of day is a good time for coffee and I can already see this will last longer than my regular coffee brand
Results.Title: Barista Style it most definitely is!

Results.ReviewText:
This was on special offer in Tesco so thought I'd give it a try, I usually buy Gold Blend anyway so didn't think it would be too much of a difference.
It's good coffee, I do like my coffee strong (like 3 tea spoons) so I was converned this would have a weaker flavour but it doesn't, it's nice, smooth ... has a bit of a smokey kind of flavour to it.  Im not sure what makes it "Barista Style" but it's a tasty coffee ... the wee tin is handy for keeping pennies in too when you're done :)
Results.Title: Good Coffee!

Results.ReviewText: I have purchased this coffee on two occasions now. I enjoy a good strong cup of coffee and have not been disappointed with this one. I am a bit fussy about my coffee, but this one definitely satisfies my needs. It is smooth, full bodied and definitely not bitter, my second favourite Nescafe product.
Results.Title: Full bodied

Results.ReviewText: This coffee has a lovely flavour really suits my taste cannot drink anything but Nescafe and only out of nescafe cups
Results.Title: Love the flavour

Results.ReviewText: Really love this coffee such an inviting aroma and the tin becomes a storage tin for allsorts
Results.Title: Fantastic taste and aroma

Results.ReviewText: I usually buy the Nescafe Gold Blend, which is smooth enough, but I spotted the Tin of Barista Style Gold Blend  and I am enjoying a cup while writing this review , even smoother and fantastic value (worth it's weight in Gold!).  Now the colder weather is taking hold, I will be making Gaelic Coffee's, with cream floating on top, just hope my hand is as smooth when I pour the Brandy, Rum, Tia Maria, Whiskey  or anything else that takes my family, friends and guests fancy! At  such good value, making 100 cups per 180g tin, I may just invite the neighbours in to!
Results.Title: Smooth finish

Results.ReviewText: ive never tried this type of coffee before so i was unsure what to expect but i was pleasently surprised. the coffee is so smooth and strong and a great way to start the day. the box is really convinient too and keeps the coffee fresh and because the flavour is so intense it last ages. although mpre procer than other brands it well worth it and definately a treat everyone should give themselves. i like mine with a dash of milk but i have served it black to guests and theyve loved it too. go out anf buy it now i promise you wont regret it!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Results.Title: tastes amazing

Results.ReviewText: Bought it so that I can take some coffee with me when going on a business trip abroad as I couldn't find strong enough coffee in the hotel room that I normally stay in. This pot is small enough to take in my luggage and convenient enough to get ready in 2 minutes and most importantly, strong enough for me to combat jet lags. Also it lasts more than one week so that I don't have to worry that it'll run out before I get back to the UK!
Results.Title: Strong enough for me

Results.ReviewText:
Nescafe's Promotion Attracted Me to try this New Product....As here in Ennis, Co Clare, we don't have an Barista ( Style ) Coffee Shops.
To My Delight, Nescafes Coffee was as Authentic a Barista Taste as one could wish for.
Its Excellent  Blend imediately gives you a Wonderful, Soft, Creamy Taste, So  as you drink it some more, it leaves you with a  Rich Sense of Satisfaction...and an Enjoyable Lingering...After Taste.
Results.Title: Exceptional True Barista Style Coffee

Results.ReviewText: First time I tried this was at a friends house so I didn't know what I was drinking at first. I asked if they had got a new coffee machine and they whipped out a tin of this stuff. SOLD! I bought a tin on my way home and now it always tops the shopping list. Nescafe Gold blend barista style has a rich, full flavour that I didn't think was possible to get from an instant coffee. Now I can have the barista experience at home in my pyjamas (as opposed to out in some expensive barista cafe in my pyjamas...) I've also since been reading some interesting articles on the Nescafe Plan which is a global initiative to support coffee farmers and develop more sustainable coffee farming so it's good to know that sales from Nescafe's range are supporting good causes.
Results.Title: Bring Barista to your home

Results.ReviewText: Our standard coffee for years now has been Gold blend (or Black, if we can get it). Now that Barista Blend has been developed, it's nicely between regular Gold Blend and real coffee bean coffee. It's only a bit more expensive than regular Gold Blend, but it's worth it!  (Life's too short for rubbish coffee!).
Results.Title: It's just that bit better than standard Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: I was given a tin of Barista coffee from a friend as she knew I loved coffee and I really fell in love with it, I did not put in my coffee jar I kept it for my treat at the end of a day, it is really smooth and you can tell instantly that you are drinking a excellent make of coffee, yum I am hooked
Results.Title: I Love it

Results.ReviewText: I thought I would try this as my usual coffee was Gold Blend, and what a heavenly treat it was. It has the full aromas of Gold Blend but with a kick of full bodied rich coffee flavour that will certainly tantalise your taste buds, a must for a coffee connoisseur.  Absolutely delicious.
Results.Title: Gold Blend Barista has the full kick

Results.ReviewText: I get this so can have a great tasting coffee in the mid afternoon, don’t always get a chance to go to coffee shops and have found this coffee a great substitute rather than buying a fancy coffee machine that would end up sitting to the side of the counter getting wasted
Results.Title: Full of Flavour

Results.ReviewText: This is one of my coffees of choice. I love it's mild but intense flavour that is so reminiscent of my local coffee shop. Black or white I love it. Perfect for my evening coffee but I will drink it any time of the day!  There is, as far as I can tell no better coffee.
Results.Title: Best coffee shop taste without any fuss

Results.ReviewText:
Always buy this, it is such a good robust coffee and the flavours and quality of  the ingredients shine through.
I am very fussy about the instant coffee that I buy but barista ticks all the boxes and the large tin lasts for ages, a good robust all rounder
Results.Title: Excellent quality and flavour

Results.ReviewText: When growing up we had Nescafé,then my Mum bought Gold Blend and we all love it, I still do ,then came Gold Blend Barista,which is fab,strong,smooth,,more like fresh coffee. I love it. I also enjoy the Crema for a change too. Actually Gold Stars from me for all 3 and in one review. Well done Nescafé. I do use all 3 ! I have the Gold Blend fountain pen and the Gold Blend long handle Gold Coffee Spoon. As you can see am a Gold Blend fan ! Would be amazing if lucky to win the Gold I phone.. Who knows
Results.Title: Definitely Gold Star Blend Coffee

Results.ReviewText:
recently away from my dolce gusto Americano pods for the weekend and bought this. delicious and well worth the price didn't miss my coffee machine for a moment. 
stored it in my locker at work, no more pricey vending machine coffees for me.
Results.Title: as good as my dolce gusto

Results.ReviewText:
I regulary buy this coffe and I would like to highlight the aroma. I love when I am making a coffie and the smell of coffe is around myself. It makes me feel back at home in Spain having breakfast in a bar before heading to the beach.
The taste is marvellous also and i enjoy sipping my very hot coffe little by little to get most of the flavour.
Affordable price, a little expensive maybe compared with other similar products but definetly worh paying a little more and have this cuality coffe.
Results.Title: Aroma

Results.ReviewText: Have been buying for quite a while now. Quality is excellent, as good as any you would get in a major coffee house chain. And the tins come in really handy for storing a variety of items after use as well!!
Results.Title: Coffee Shop Quality

Results.ReviewText: i bought gold blend barista for when friends come round and my elevensies it smells divine and tastes rich and dark and smooth all in one and was better than i expected
Results.Title: how to be a barista

Results.ReviewText: Love the tin, so easy to open and store the coffee. Love the aroma as hot water hits the cup, goes down like velvet, makes that coffee moment extra special.
Results.Title: Exceptional experience

Results.ReviewText: When you have a had a busy day and you have a five minutes to yourself grab a cup of fantastic cup of coffee out of this world...
Results.Title: what a coffee....

Results.ReviewText: I have stated using this item recently and find it to be very good quality. Smooth and Rich. Drink more coffee at home now
Results.Title: Coffee shop quality

Results.ReviewText: This tin is great value and great quality all rolled into one...what more can you ask.Start your day the Gold way.
Results.Title: Value for money..quality coffee

Results.ReviewText: Great taste with a very strong flavour  and smells wonderful
Results.Title: GREAT taste

Results.ReviewText: Best coffee so smooth and rich glad I bought it when I did
Results.Title: Great Flavour
